      • toCSVString

        public String toCSVString()
        This method turns the Period into a line which can be saved into a csv file. The format is as follows: The cells are sperated by a ';'. The first cell denotes the setup cost parameter and the second one the inventory holdin cost parameter. The following cells denote the order distributions represented by two cells with the mean and the standard deviation. The order cells are in the same sequence as in getOrderDistributions().
        Returns:
        a CSV string representation of the period
